						<summary>

						<p>Damaged. States that, while <hi rend="bold">Komaragiri-Reḍḍi</hi> was King and <hi rend="bold">Chokkana Siṅgana</hi> was governor of <hi rend="bold">Taṅgeḍa,</hi> the said Siṅgana and certain persons referred to as <hi rend="italic">chālumūla-vubhaya-nānādēśāla pekkaṇḍru</hi> made gifts of land and customs duties to god Gōpinātha.</p>						

						</summary>
